parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked turbocharger intake can cause rough engine idle, stalling, and reduced engine power.
Engine sputtering on cold starts can cause the vehicle to enter "get home" mode, limiting engine performance and potentially leading to engine damage.
Engine stalling or RPM drop can cause loss of control, increasing the risk of accidents.

The failure of the battery charging system can cause the battery to overcharge or drain excessively, leading to catastrophic battery failure, which may result in a fire. This can also impede egress from the vehicle in severe weather conditions and affect the vehicle's ability to provide warmth or cooling to occupants.
symptoms: even when the vehicle is used regularly; excessive buildup of copper sulfate and corrosion on the positive battery terminal; battery failure within a short period (less than 2 years).
